    <h1>Cat Care Tips</h1>
    <p>Welcome to our Cat Care Tips page. Here, you'll find essential guidelines and resources on how to care for your cat. For comprehensive details, please visit the recommended links.</p>

    <h2>Feeding Your Cat</h2>
    <p>Choose a well-balanced diet for your cat's age and health status. Fresh water should always be available. <a href="https://www.aspca.org/pet-care/cat-care/cat-nutrition-tips">More on feeding your cat.</a></p>

    <h2>Enrichment</h2>
    <p>Play and stimulation are vital for your cat's well-being. Provide toys, scratching posts, and interactive playtime. <a href="https://www.humanesociety.org/resources/enriching-your-cats-life">Ideas for cat enrichment.</a></p>

    <h2>Healthcare</h2>
    <p>Regular vet check-ups are important for preventative care and vaccinations. Pay attention to any changes in behavior or health. <a href="https://www.avma.org/resources-tools/pet-owners/petcare/cat-care">Cat health resources.</a></p>

    <h2>Litter Box Training</h2>
    <p>Maintain a clean litter box and place it in a quiet, accessible location. Some cats may prefer a specific type of litter. <a href="https://www.aspca.org/pet-care/cat-care/common-cat-behavior-issues/litter-box-problems">Litter box tips.</a></p>
